  "body": "With the redesign of the compact mode, we added a new background color change on hover, which required a MouseArea over all of the Message. It works very well and still enabled the click events to permeate to the message (you can still click links and select text).\n\nHowever, it did break the hover effect we had on links in the text. This means that hovering links doesn't change the mouse to a pointer, nor do is show the \"text selection\" pointer over normal text.\n\nQML is not the best at handling MouseAreas over other MouseAreas, so this might be a tricky task.",
